.TH BASEFWX 7 "May 2026" "BaseFWX 3.6.4" "BaseFWX Manual"
.SH NAME
basefwx \- C++ cryptographic codec library and container family
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
#include <basefwx/basefwx.hpp>

pkg-config --cflags --libs basefwx

find_package(basefwx CONFIG REQUIRED)
target_link_libraries(app PRIVATE basefwx::basefwxcpp)
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
BaseFWX is a cryptographic codec toolkit. It protects files, byte streams,
and selected media carrier formats. It is not a network transport by itself
and it does not provide anonymity by itself.
.PP
Applications such as YUME use BaseFWX as an inner cryptographic and encoding
layer. The C++ library provides authenticated encryption, password hardening,
post-quantum key encapsulation when built with liboqs support, live stream
framing, and media carrier helpers.
.PP
The Debian packaging in this source tree ships the C++ CLI, shared library,
and development files as separate binary packages from one source package.
It does not install the Python or Java modules.
.SH BASIC FLOW
.nf
+--------------------------------+
|  CALLER                        |
|  CLI / library / YUME          |
+--------------------------------+
        |
        | password, bytes, options
        v
+--------------------------------+
|  BASEFWX CORE                  |
|  KDF, keys, AEAD, metadata     |
+--------------------------------+
        |
        | encrypted container
        v
+--------------------------------+
|  OUTPUT FORMAT                 |
|  file, packet, media carrier   |
+--------------------------------+
        |
        | stored or transported
        v
+--------------------------------+
|  DECODER                       |
|  verifies before release       |
+--------------------------------+
.fi
.PP
The caller supplies plaintext bytes and a password or key context. BaseFWX
derives or unwraps encryption keys, encrypts and authenticates the payload,
and writes a format another BaseFWX implementation can parse.
.PP
On decode, BaseFWX reads authenticated metadata, derives or unwraps the same
keys, verifies integrity, and releases plaintext only after verification
passes.
.SH CODEC FAMILIES
.TP
.B fwxAES
AES-GCM file encryption with metadata and optional wrappers.
.TP
.B pb512 / b512
Password-backed heavy encodings and file modes.
.TP
.B livecipher
Packetized stream encryption for pipes and transport use.
.TP
.B keywrap / pq
Password and master-key wrapping helpers, including ML-KEM-768 when liboqs
support is enabled.
.TP
.B kFM / jMG
Strict media carrier encode/decode and media cipher flows.
.TP
.B n10 / b256 / b512
Reversible text and binary encodings.
.SH FILE CONTAINERS
.nf
+--------------------------------+
|  PLAINTEXT FILE                |
|  bytes from disk or stdin      |
+--------------------------------+
        |
        v
+--------------------------------+
|  KDF AND KEY SETUP             |
|  Argon2id or PBKDF2            |
+--------------------------------+
        |
        v
+--------------------------------+
|  AEAD ENCRYPTION               |
|  AES-256-GCM + metadata        |
+--------------------------------+
        |
        | ===>
        v
+--------------------------------+
|  BASEFWX CONTAINER             |
|  FWX1 / heavy / encoded form   |
+--------------------------------+
.fi
.PP
At a high level, encrypted file containers carry authenticated metadata and
encrypted payload bytes:
.nf
+----------------------------------------------------------------------+
|  BASEFWX ENCRYPTED CONTAINER                                         |
|                                                                      |
|  magic/version | KDF parameters | wrap data | metadata | ciphertext  |
|                                                                      |
|  metadata is authenticated; payload releases after verification      |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------+
.fi
.PP
Exact byte layout depends on the selected codec family. Use the public API
to read and write containers instead of hand-parsing container fields.
.SH LIVE STREAMS
.nf
+--------------------------------+
|  PRODUCER                      |
|  file, ffmpeg, app bytes       |
+--------------------------------+
        |
        v
+--------------------------------+
|  LIVE ENCRYPTOR                |
|  start, update, finalize       |
+--------------------------------+
        |
        | ===>
        v
+--------------------------------+
|  LIVE PACKETS                  |
|  ordered AES-GCM frames        |
+--------------------------------+
        |
        v
+--------------------------------+
|  LIVE DECRYPTOR                |
|  verifies packet sequence      |
+--------------------------------+
.fi
.PP
Live mode emits packetized frames, keeping memory bounded for pipes,
sockets, and transport integrations. Receivers must process frames in order
and finalize before treating the stream as complete.
.SH YUME INTEGRATION
.nf
+--------------------------------+
|  YUME STREAM                   |
|  logical app connection        |
+--------------------------------+
        |
        v
+--------------------------------+
|  BASEFWX INNER CRYPTO          |
|  AES / Argon2id / ML-KEM       |
+--------------------------------+
        |
        | ===>
        v
+--------------------------------+
|  YUME CARRIER                  |
|  TLS 1.3 + YUME frames         |
+--------------------------------+
        |
        v
+--------------------------------+
|  YUMED SERVER                  |
|  unwraps inner stream data     |
+--------------------------------+
.fi
.PP
For packaged YUME builds, the yume binary links against libbasefwx.so.3
through the libbasefwx-dev build package and the libbasefwx3 runtime package.
.SH PACKAGE LAYOUT
.nf
+--------------------------------+
|  basefwx                       |
|  command-line frontend         |
+--------------------------------+
        |
        v
+--------------------------------+
|  libbasefwx3                   |
|  runtime shared library        |
+--------------------------------+
        ^
        |
+--------------------------------+
|  libbasefwx-dev                |
|  headers and build metadata    |
+--------------------------------+
        ^
        |
+--------------------------------+
|  yume                          |
|  links to libbasefwx.so.3      |
+--------------------------------+
.fi
.PP
Local development builds may use a prepared vendor liboqs staging directory
to keep ML-KEM-768 available. Debian archive builds should use a normal
packaged liboqs-dev dependency instead of embedding liboqs into BaseFWX.
.SH FAILURE MODEL
BaseFWX should fail closed. A wrong password, changed ciphertext, missing
PQ support for PQ-required containers, non-carrier media input, or truncated
live stream should fail instead of releasing unauthenticated plaintext.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/include/basefwx/
C++ public headers.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/<multiarch>/libbasefwx.so.3
BaseFWX runtime shared library.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/<multiarch>/cmake/basefwx/
CMake package files.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/<multiarch>/pkgconfig/basefwx.pc
pkg-config metadata.
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/libbasefwx3/EXPLAINED.md.gz
Extended overview with reusable diagrams.
